<item>
            <title>[SEC-1277] The authorization tag libraries are totally wrong!</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1277</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;security:authorize ifAllGranted=&quot;ROLE_SUPERVISOR&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;td&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;a href=&quot;del.htm?id=&amp;lt;c:out value=&quot;$&lt;/p&gt;
{contact.id}&quot;/&amp;gt;&quot;&amp;gt;Del&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/security:authorize&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I think it is more reasonable to protect a resource like this&#65306;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;security:authorize ifAllAuthorised=&quot;&lt;b&gt;del&lt;/b&gt;.htm&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;td&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;a href=&quot;del.htm?id=&amp;lt;c:out value=&quot;${contact.id}
&lt;p&gt;&quot;/&amp;gt;&quot;&amp;gt;Del&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/security:authorize&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because the relationship between resources and roles may change in the future,&lt;br/&gt;
even more,the role name may change.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
